<paragraph id="8B8536EB5B705004FF2FFD6236EF5D81" blockId="1.[148,977,604,944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
The 
<typeStatus id="548188495B705004FF54FD62371E5CC7" box="[215,302,737,758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">lectotype</typeStatus>
(SBL 
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FEEEFD62374F5CC4" bold="true" box="[365,383,737,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">¼</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CC29B0E5B705004FE07FD6237E15CC7" box="[388,465,737,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="5.6">5.6 mm</quantity>
; ABL 
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FD8CFD6234115CC4" bold="true" box="[527,545,737,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">¼</emphasis>
about 6.0 mm) belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B705004FCCAFD62354D5CC7" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[841,893,737,758]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FCCAFD62354D5CC7" box="[841,893,737,758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. I cannot associate it with any species described by Allen (1972) but by its size and shape of pronotum, particularly the non protruding front angles, it looks more similar to members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B705004FE89FCB337935D74" authority="Allen" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[266,419,816,837]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algidus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FE89FCB337595D74" box="[266,361,816,837]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. algidus</emphasis>
Allen
</taxonomicName>
than to any other species seen. It differs from the 
<typeStatus id="548188495B705004FCFEFCB335E05D74" box="[893,976,816,837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D3CFD625B705004FF41FCC837725D51" box="[194,322,843,864]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">one paratype</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B705004FEECFCC837E55D51" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[367,469,843,864]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algidus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FEECFCC837E55D51" box="[367,469,843,864]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. algidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
studied in having the antennae and legs entirely yellowish (
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FF7CFCE537235D4B" bold="true" box="[255,275,870,890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">6</emphasis>
reddish-black in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D685B705004FE3FFCE6342C5D4B" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[444,540,869,890]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algidus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAF95B705004FE3FFCE6342C5D4B" box="[444,540,869,890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">L. algidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the elytral striae slightly shallower and less coarsely punctate, and the microsculpture on the proepisternum and metepisternum coarser.
</paragraph>
